App Walkthrough / Roadmap

Certificate issuance
1. Institution register with Institution details
2. Institution issue certificate by entering students credential details 
3. Credential is issued by storing the details and computing a Hashfunction and using the hash value to generate a Qr code on certificate
5. The Hash value is then stored in the blockchain using Hyperledger (generating a smart contract to seal the transaction)
6. Then the PDF is downloaded by Institution Admin

Certificate Verification by External verifier
1. External verifier registers with basic info 
2. He clicks on the verify Qr button
3. A QR scanner pops up and scans QR code on certificate
4. The app verifies the certificate and shows if certificate is valid or not and maybe suspended or revoked or active 


Certificate Verification by graduate
1. Graduate registers with his info as a student of an institution
2. He clicks on the verify Qr button
3. A QR scanner pops up and scans QR code on certificate
4. The app verifies the certificate and shows if certificate is valid or not and maybe suspended or revoked or active 

